  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0daf \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d85\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0db0\u0dd4\u0dbb \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dca\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d9a\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dcf\u0dba\u0db8 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d85\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0dba\u0dd2?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Is Basil's group against the President's budget or the state ministries with privileges?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sunday Times reports that the group supporting Mr. Basil Rajapaksa of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna has stated that if privileges are not granted to the ministers to be appointed in the future, they will vote against the budget to be presented by President Ranil Wickremesinghe as the Minister of Finance on the 30th.",
        "Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna still has the majority in Parliament. Thus they have stated that the state ministers have a private secretary, a press secretary and three coordination secretaries and all five of them have separate vehicles.",
        "In addition, state ministers are entitled to five office staff members, three vehicles and other perks enjoyed by ministers. Also, their salaries will be equal to the salaries of ministers.",
        "The Sunday Time newspaper, which mentions that President Ranil Wickremesinghe is currently preparing the list of state ministers, has not yet made a final decision on how many state ministers will be appointed.",
        "Since the state ministers are to be appointed before the presentation of the interim budget and the appointment of an all-party government has become a bit of a problem, it has become complicated to appoint the new cabinet.",
        "The focus is on going forward by including the existing cabinet and several other parties and such inclusion will naturally lead to a rift between the government and the parties concerned."
      ],
